text:
RT @nprpolitics: In the 2000 election, the Electoral College outcome was 271-266 — the closest electoral vote margin since 1876. If Biden's leads hold in this election, he's on track to win 306 electoral votes to Trump's 232.

The situations aren't even close to the same.

name: NPR
text:
While votes are still being counted in Georgia, President-elect Joe Biden — who holds a 14,000-vote lead — is favored to win.

"I don't think there's any doubt we have beat Donald Trump by 14,000," says the CEO of Fair Fight Action.

text: After a purge of top Pentagon officials, former national security officials fear the fallout if Trump were to launch an unprovoked military action against Iran or make big changes in Afghanistan in his final days in office. https://t.co/3jE0Zklwuv
